<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/200:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName corresp="#p_MJT1" type="from">Marriner</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-29T19:00:00+00:00">November
                                    29, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 29—5:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>679. From <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Norman Davis</persName>. I have
                            just learned that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MJR1">MacDonald</persName>
                            and <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John Simon</persName> are leaving
                                Thursday<note n="97" xml:id="d330fn97">December 1.</note> and expect
                            to arrive in Geneva on Friday morning. Previous to this <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> had informed me in writing that
                            the Prime Minister had told him that when he went to Geneva he would
                            like an opportunity to discuss with the representatives of the other
                            principal powers the situation in regard to the proposed world economic
                            conference and <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> has so
                            informed <persName corresp="#p_NBCv1">von Neurath</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PJ2">Paul-Boncour</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_ABP1">Aloisi</persName>. He stated that he <pb facs="0607" n="487" xml:id="pg_487"/> was doing this “so that we may
                            be all prepared for some discussion on the subject”.</p>
                        <p>I plan to return to Geneva tomorrow, Wednesday, night. [<persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MJT1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marriner</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>